    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="524"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d524">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/1011</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Secretary of Labor</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-09">November 9,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In further reply to your letter of September 12,
                        1929,<note n="97" xml:id="d524fn97">Not printed.</note> regarding the
                    proposed deportation to Mexico of … I desire to inform you that this Department
                    has received specific advices from Mexican official sources to the effect that …
                    is wanted in Mexico for alleged revolutionary activities, and that, if he should
                    enter Mexico, he will be apprehended and tried on charges of having been
                    involved in the insurrection of March and April last. In view of this
                    circumstance it is requested that … be not deported to Mexico at this time.</p>
                <p>The file attached to your letter of September 12 is herewith returned.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Trusler Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
